    <h3>Ready to start?</h3>
    <p>1. Select Sign In: A new folder will be created on Your Google Drive called FieldData.info</p>
    <p>2. Complete a template: Press templates button, pick a template and submit it.</p>
    <p>3. Find Your data: Open <a href="https://drive.google.com/drive/my-drive" target="_blank">Your Google Drive</a> and check out the folder FieldData.info to find your new data.</p>
    <p>4. Build a report: Go to our <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/fielddatainfo" target="_blank">forum</a> to find out how to build time saving applications using FieldData.info!</p>
    <p>5. Build a custom template: Ask us how on the <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/fielddatainfo" target="_blank">forum</a>.</p>

    <hr />
    <h3>Features</h3>
    <p>You own and control all of Your data on Your Google account.</p>
    <p>Data is collected and stored in realtime so your organisation can respond to change rapidly.</p>
    <p>You can build your own reports, event engines, and complex data analysis using the familar Google interface.</p>
    <p>Need some guidance on Google Spreadsheets? Check out this <a href="https://www.google.com.au/sheets/about/" target="_blank">reference</a>.</p>

    <hr />
    <h3>Pricing</h3>
    <p>Unlimited usage of templates.</p>
    <p>Custom template licences are AUD$50 per template per user per year.</p>
    <p>Ask about discounts for bulk orders.</p>
    <p>We can build custom templates from AUD$1000 (or you can build your own, <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/fielddatainfo" target="_blank">ask us how</a>)</p>
    <p>Email and phone support can be purchased.</p>

    <hr />
    <h3>Security</h3>
    <p>We take security very seriously.</p>
    <p>This application only stores Your information on Your Google drive.</p>
    <p>Access will only be requested to resources created by this application and some basic profile data.</p>
    <p>In other words, this app will not attempt to access any private content on Your Google account.</p>
    <p>Unfortunately at this time we need to request access to all Spreadsheets because the Google scope system does not have an option for only spreadsheets created by an application.</p>
    <p>This site requests the following <a href="https://developers.google.com/identity/protocols/googlescopes" target="_blank">Google Scopes</a> userinfo.profile; drive.file; drive.appfolder and spreadsheets</p>
    <p><a href="https://security.google.com/settings/security/permissions?pli=1" target="_blank">Revoke Access</a> at any time.</p>

