    <h3>FAQ</h3>
    <p>Q. Does FieldData.info charge to submit a template?</p>
    <p>A. No. FieldData.info does not impose any limits or charges when You submit a template.</p>
    <hr/>
    <p>Q. Does FieldData.info handle complex form data such as nested form elements?</p>
    <p>A. Yes. We use dot notation to store it.</p>
    <hr />
    <p>Q. Is there a limit on file size?</p>
    <p>A. No limit is imposed, however be aware large photos can take some time to transfer over slow links and there may be a data cost associated with your mobile carrier. There are a number of techniques to avoid this issue such as setting Your phone photo settings to a lower resolution.</p>
    <hr />
    <p>Q. Can I build my own custom templates?</p>
    <p>A. Yes. Ask us how on the <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/fielddatainfo" target="_blank">forum</a>.</p>
    <hr />
    <p>Q. Can I hide my custom templates from other FieldData.info users?</p>
    <p>A. Yes. Ask us how on the <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/fielddatainfo" target="_blank">forum</a>.</p>
    <hr />
    <p>Q. Can I save data to another FieldData.info users Google Drive?</p>
    <p>A. You could. But it is easy to merge data from multiple Google sheets by using the Google Sheets ImportRange function, so we recommend you do that instead.</p>
